ege during the last few decades as a result of structural changes in the health care system. Starting with the pluralization of values in modern societies, a new debate has been launched about the place of conscientious objection in providing medical services. The volume approaches this problem from an interdisciplinary perspective and elucidates the diverse dimensions of decisions of conscience.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aHealthxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aMedical ethics. 7aRELIGION / Theology.2bisacsh  aEthics.  aclinical equipoise.  aconscience.  ahealth care.1 aBaumann, Klaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBecker, Gerhild, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBentele, Katrin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBergdolt, Klaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBormann, Franz-Josef, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBormann, Franz-Josef, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBuch, Alois Joh., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDuttge, Gunnar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEibach, Ulrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErnst, Stephan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFonk, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aForschner, Maximilian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrick, Eckhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGertrud, Nunner-Winkler, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGiese, Constanze, econtributor.